<div class="playground">
    <header class="playground-header">
        <div class="header-top">
            <a class="home-link" href="/">← SoundScript</a>
            <span class="badge">Playground · @VersionInfo.Label</span>
        </div>
        <h1>SoundScript Playground</h1>
        <p class="lead">Type SoundScript V2, compile to MIDI, and hear it in your browser — fully client-side.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="presets">
        <span class="preset-label">Example:</span>
        <select class="example-select" @bind="SelectedExampleKey" @bind:after="LoadSelectedExample">
            <optgroup label="V2">
                <option value="v2-showcase">Showcase</option>
                <option value="v2-blocks">Blocks</option>
                <option value="v2-metadata">Metadata</option>
                <option value="v2-tempo">Tempo</option>
                <option value="v2-layers">Layers</option>
                <option value="v2-humanize">Humanize</option>
                <option value="v2-chords">Chords+</option>
                <option value="v2-phrases">Phrases</option>
                <option value="v2-phrases-v3">Phrases V3</option>
                <option value="v2-patterns">Patterns</option>
                <option value="v2-orchestration">Orchestration</option>
                <option value="v2-voice">Voice</option>
            </optgroup>
            <optgroup label="Core">
                <option value="core-melody">Melody</option>
                <option value="core-articulations">Articulations</option>
                <option value="core-dynamics">Dynamics</option>
                <option value="core-chords">Chords</option>
                <option value="core-intelligence">Intelligence</option>
                <option value="core-multitrack">Multi-track</option>
                <option value="core-playback">Playback</option>
            </optgroup>
            <!-- UNDER DEVELOPMENT — v3: these examples use wave-only grammar
                 (effect/speak, humanize's named form); Run detects it in the
                 AST and renders via SoundScript.Wave instead of MIDI. -->
            <optgroup label="Wave (.ssw)">
                <option value="wave-effects">Effects (delay + filter)</option>
                <option value="wave-speak">Speak (prosody tone)</option>
                <option value="wave-humanize">Seeded humanize + speak</option>
            </optgroup>
        </select>
    </div>

    <div class="presets">
        <span class="preset-label">Text-to-Melody:</span>
        <input class="compose-input"
               @bind="ComposeText"
               spellcheck="false"
               placeholder="Type plain text to compose from" />
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" disabled="@IsRunning" @onclick="ComposeFromTextAsync">Compose from text</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" disabled="@IsRunning" @onclick="ComposeWithProsodyAsync">Compose with Prosody</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" disabled="@IsRunning" @onclick="RenderAudioAsync">Render Audio</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" disabled="@IsRunning" @onclick="RenderAudioWithProsodyAsync">Render Audio (Prosody)</button>
    </div>

    <div class="panes">
        <section class="pane pane-editor">
            <label class="pane-label" for="script-input">SoundScript</label>
            <textarea id="script-input"
                      class="script-input"
                      @bind="ScriptText"
                      spellcheck="false"
                      placeholder="track melody { ... }"></textarea>
        </section>

        <section class="pane pane-output">
            <label class="pane-label">Output</label>

            @* UNDER DEVELOPMENT — v3: grammar-isolation rule — only rendered
               when the last Run actually took the SoundScript.Wave rail
               (AST contained an EffectNode/SpeakNode), never unconditionally. *@
            @if (UsedWaveBackend)
            {
                <span class="badge">SoundScript.Wave · no MIDI step</span>
            }

            <div class="actions">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" disabled="@IsRunning" @onclick="RunAsync">
                    @(IsRunning ? "Running…" : "Run")
                </button>
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" @onclick="StopAsync">Stop</button>
                @if (MidiBytes is not null)
                {
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" @onclick="DownloadAsync">Download MIDI</button>
                }
                @if (WavBytes is not null)
                {
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" @onclick="DownloadWavAsync">Download WAV</button>
                }
                @if (SsText is not null)
                {
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" @onclick="DownloadSsAsync">Download .ss</button>
                }
            </div>

            @if (SsText is not null)
            {
                <details class="ss-preview">
                    <summary>View .ss source</summary>
                    <pre>@SsText</pre>
                </details>
            }

            @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(StatusMessage))
            {
                <div class="status" role="status">@StatusMessage</div>
            }

            @if (WarningMessages.Count > 0)
            {
                <div class="warning" role="status">
                    <strong>Warnings</strong>
                    <ul>
                        @foreach (var warning in WarningMessages)
                        {
                            <li>@warning</li>
                        }
                    </ul>
                </div>
            }

            @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(ErrorMessage))
            {
                <div class="error" role="alert">
                    <strong>Error</strong>
                    <pre>@ErrorMessage</pre>
                </div>
            }

            <div class="pipeline">
                <span>Tokenizer</span>
                <span class="arrow">→</span>
                <span>Parser</span>
                <span class="arrow">→</span>
                <span>Interpreter</span>
                <span class="arrow">→</span>
                <span>PhraseTimingShaper</span>
                <span class="arrow">→</span>
                <span>PhraseShaper</span>
                <span class="arrow">→</span>
                <span>PatternExpander</span>
                <span class="arrow">→</span>
                <span>Orchestration</span>
                <span class="arrow">→</span>
                <span>Layers</span>
                <span class="arrow">→</span>
                <span>Humanize</span>
                <span class="arrow">→</span>
                <span>MIDI</span>
                <span class="arrow">+</span>
                <span>Voice</span>
                <span class="arrow">+</span>
                <span>PhonemeComposer</span>
                <span class="arrow">+</span>
                <span>ProsodyComposer</span>
                <span class="arrow">→</span>
                <span>SoundCSS</span>
                <span class="arrow">→</span>
                <span>Timbre</span>
            </div>

            @* UNDER DEVELOPMENT — v3: shown only when Run actually took the
               wave rail (grammar-isolation rule — see the badge above). *@
            @if (UsedWaveBackend)
            {
                <div class="pipeline">
                    <span>Tokenizer</span>
                    <span class="arrow">→</span>
                    <span>Parser</span>
                    <span class="arrow">→</span>
                    <span>SoundScript.Wave</span>
                    <span class="arrow">+</span>
                    <span>MasterEffectChain</span>
                    <span class="arrow">+</span>
                    <span>ProsodyToneGenerator</span>
                    <span class="arrow">→</span>
                    <span>WAV</span>
                </div>
            }

            <p class="hint">
                No server, no API calls. Imports use the CLI (<code>ProgramLoader</code>); all other V2 features run here.
                <code>voice</code> blocks speak their lyrics through your browser's speech synthesis while the melody plays —
                the downloaded MIDI carries the lyrics as standard karaoke events.
                <strong>Compose from text</strong> runs the deterministic <code>PhonemeComposer</code>
                (text → syllables → phonemes → gestures → MIDI): the same text always produces the same MIDI bytes.
                <strong>Compose with Prosody</strong> runs the V5 <code>ProsodyComposer</code> instead — pitch is
                planned top-down (phrase → word → syllable) so the melody follows spoken stress and sentence
                contour rather than a fixed pitch per phoneme.
                <strong>Render Audio</strong> adds the V4 offline timbre pass (MIDI → SoundCSS → WAV) — slow-motion synthesis, not real-time playback.
                <strong>Render Audio (Prosody)</strong> runs the same offline timbre pass over the <code>ProsodyComposer</code> MIDI instead —
                same phoneme timbre, word/syllable-shaped pitch.
                Both compose buttons also produce an editable <strong>.ss</strong> export (V6) — view it inline,
                download it, hand-tweak a note, and run it through <code>soundscript run</code> to hear exactly your edit.
                <strong>Run</strong> also understands wave-only grammar (<code>effect delay/filter</code>, <code>speak</code>,
                and <code>humanize</code>'s named <code>timing=/velocity=/seed=</code> form) — a script using any of it
                skips MIDI entirely and renders straight to WAV through <strong>SoundScript.Wave</strong>, byte-identical
                for the same script text every time. Everything else still plays through MIDI, unchanged.
                <code>seed=</code> is optional on both <code>humanize</code> and <code>speak</code> — leaving it out
                doesn't mean random, it means the seed is derived from the track name or spoken text instead of an
                explicit number, so the render still reproduces exactly the same way every time.
                → <a href="/doc.html?p=wave-grammar.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">.ssw grammar reference</a>.
            </p>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>
